main event: A circular object larger than 8/c with a shimmering outline was observed off the North Coast of Labrador, reportedly traveling at high speeds and disappearing behind low clouds.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 2-3 minutes,The object made no sound,Several possible explanations were suggested including a balloon and conventional aircraft,The object was seen from multiple vessels in the area,The report includes detailed coordinates of the ships involved in the observation.
location: Off North Coast Labrador, Newfoundland and Labrador, CA
witness description: one observer was the third mate of the ship 'Algairen' and another was the first mate of the ship 'Gannett'
